<br>
For the last week I have been incredibly frustrated. It seems that times are changing, at least on Kane Bale, and grouping is going out of style. I can spend an hour in the pok spamming, &quot;Level 41 ench. lfg&quot; with no avail. What I have been resorting to is my good friend. He is a Cleric and we make a good team, root nuke combo. At any rate, I count always count on him to be ready to duo with me. <br>
<br>
To get to the point of frustration, I have been trying to hit 44 desperately, and after playing non-stop for the past week I've done nothing but meerly lvl one lvl. When I can't find a good group worth my time, I go and charm EW. Man-O-Wars make amazing pets, but exp. is incredibly slow. The real reason for this slow xp is that I always get ambushed by Frost Giants guarding Kael, something that was new to me until I died from them. Please could someone give me some advice on how and where to solo, I desperately need it!!! I think my charming technique is rather good. I mez, tash, charm, haste, then guard and pull to my pet, rooting the mob. However I need a better spot or better zone to do this in. Thank you for your time and concern.<br>
<br>
Sarcomium<br>
41 Enchanter <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dalur>Dalur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#330000>(4/24/03 11:50:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing</span><hr size=1> If you want to try to solo without doing the charm thing, you could try to solo the lone spectre in Feerrott before you get to the cave that leads to fear.<br>
<br>
However, at your level, you will definitely want to make sure you pull away from the cave or you will agro the one inside and have 2 of them to deal with.  The respawn is about 6 and half mins I think.  They are decent xp up to about 49-50.  Also if you get the normal scythes, they sell for about 11 pp each.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kristanatruefyre>KristanaTruefyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#330000>(4/24/03 1:57:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing</span><hr size=1> ya, Feerott is a great place, or if you have LoY, Gunthak, is great XP, I leveled my monk 2 levels there in a day. if you have a cleric that you duo with, thats great, but you can usually find a group there within a matter of minutes. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://stratosd.homestead.com/files/Xandollf_Kristana.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=102642"> Magelo Profile</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=charmroxors>Charmroxors</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#330000>(4/24/03 3:24:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing</span><hr size=1> at 41 you could charm solo in EW great... dont stay too close to the Kael zone line, the kromrif death squad spawns there as part of the coldain prayer shawl quests. stay near the hut w/ the ghost coldain guy, you can charm walruses there easily, there are tons of them so the downtime will mostly be waiting on mana. <br>
<br>
you could probably do DL as well, use the drolvargs as pets and charm kite your way through the zone =)  <br>
<br>
GD is also good, giants make good pets, they smash through the wolves quite easily when hasted. <br>
<br>
 <p>Charmroxors<br>
60chanter<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=555166" target="_new">my gear</a>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taeldansilvershade>Taeldan Silvershade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(4/25/03 4:09:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Question</span><hr size=1> Maybe I am doing this wrong and someone can help. I have been trying hard to get used to playing a chanter solo. I got int of 244 and cha of 206 after I swap primary I got int of 233 and cha of 231. I figured that it would be enough to solo in PoN. Well let me give example of my soloing ability:<br>
<br>
See treant and charm......treant become my little death soldier. Then cast haste on my new pet. Sick pet on a mob....as he is fighting I then cast tash, root, slow on mob. Wait till mob is dead....if like 7 out of 10 times my pet turns on me. Now I go and sick pet after another mob....with luck that after this long having pet my charm hasn't broken....which almost always does then I am stuck with a pet that is almost dead and need mana. Pet breaks my charm.....try to recharm...hmm not enough time before he hits me breaking my cast (I use bedlam also) and I am running to zone. <br>
<br>
I am excited about trying to solo....and willing to try anything but I can't seem to keep my pet undercontrol. Could I get some tips on what I am doing wrong? I am a level 58 chanter and should be able to solo yard trash in PoN. But just keep loosing charm and having problems geting mob undercontrol again...or being able to get my mana back. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=astyd>astyd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 93<br> <font color=#330000>(4/25/03 5:05:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question</span><hr size=1> <br>
2 comments.<br>
<br>
1 - Tash your pet before you charm him<br>
<br>
2 - To facilitate 1, I always mez pets then tash then charm.<br>
<br>
3 - Get a horse/lizard and med during the fight.<br>
<br>
4 - Make sure the target mob (not pet) is rooted during the fight.  (Thus only have one mob on you during the fight).<br>
<br>
5 - Others do this differently, but I use Torment of Argli (or at my level Torment of Scio) to do the damage to the mob.  I have never had these break root (but Asyphixate/Strangle does regularly).<br>
<br>
6 - I mezz recontrol the pet on a break.  Its a lot more likely to work than charm.<br>
<br>
Cames Houdini<br>
Level 64 Chanter - Vazelle<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=candiarie>Candiarie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#330000>(4/25/03 6:08:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question</span><hr size=1> I found in my little experience that treants dont like being charmed.  I tend to use spiders, but thats just personal preference for yard trash, birds work too.  The 4 times ive tried charming treants it never works too well, breaks within the minute. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=113663" target="top">Candiarie Wyldefyre</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->&quot;&gt; [55 Beguiler]  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.guildportal.com/Guild.asp?GuildID=355&amp;TabID=337">Ring of Xev</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=simonj621>SimonJ621</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#330000>(4/30/03 4:11:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing</span><hr size=1> Since my post I have been practicing my solo skill. I have found a great place for low 40's. If you have the LoY expansion you may want to try soling the beach in Gunthak. The best pet I have yet to find is a Niflik or something like that. It is a purple bug looking mob. With haste on him, I can bash through any mob on the beach. And when there is a named, I slow the named and throw some runes on my pet. This method also works well with a Cleric or Druid partner. Just wanted to give an update on my progress.<br>
<br>
Sarcomium<br>
